{
  "question_id": "43c9daa7-25c1-4d09-90d1-18864e5996aa",
  "short_text": "Digit 6",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print the digit **6** in `2 * N - 1` rows using stars (`*`).\n\n```\n* * * \n*    \n* * * \n*   * \n* * * \n```\n\n<MultiLineNote>\nThere is a space after every star (`*`).\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `2 * N - 1` rows containing stars (`*`) as the digit **6** shown in the sample output.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 4`, \n\n- Print the stars (`*`) on **7** (`2 * 4 - 1`) rows as shown in the given image.\n\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-digit-6.png' widthPercent='50'/>\n\n<MultiLineNote>\n\nIn the given image,\n\n- The Empty box indicates two spaces (\"&nbsp;&nbsp;\").\n- The Star in the box indicates the star and a space (\"* \").\n\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n* * * * \n*      \n*      \n* * * * \n*     * \n*     * \n* * * * \n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "f994c3f0-c932-4bc7-89e9-ea9c049872ab",
      "code_content": "n = int(input())\n\nfor row in range(1, 2 * n):\n    if row == 1 or row == n or row == (2 * n - 1):\n        each_row = \"* \" * n\n    elif row < n :\n        each_row = \"* \"\n    else:\n        spaces = \" \" * (2 * (n - 2))\n        each_row = \"* \" + spaces + \"* \"\n        \n    print(each_row)\n    ",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
